      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>1907-1974. S.A.Hessel served as a research associate in th department of entomology at the Yale University Peabody Museum. He is known for his collecting trip to Africa in 1960 as well as his work with lepodoptera in Conecticut.</p>  
      </bioghist>
